  "instructions": [
    "Preheat your oven to 350°F (175°C).",
    "Slice the rye bread into thin layers.",
    "In a mixing bowl, combine lemon juice, orange juice, honey or agave syrup, flaxseed meal, caster sugar, and ground cinnamon. Mix well until no lumps remain.",
    "Coat each slice of rye bread with the citrusy batter, ensuring an even layer on both sides.",
    "Place the coated slices on a baking tray lined with parchment paper.",
    "Bake in preheated oven for 10-15 minutes or until golden brown and crispy.",
    "Remove from oven and let it cool slightly before serving."
